    diagnostics: ["DNA methylation analysis at 15q11-q13 (first-line screening test — detects all three mechanisms)", "FISH or chromosomal microarray to confirm paternal deletion", "Microsatellite/SNP analysis to identify maternal UPD", "Growth hormone stimulation testing (most PWS patients are GH deficient)", "Polysomnography (sleep study) before and during GH therapy", "Fasting glucose, HbA1c, lipid panel (metabolic screening for obesity complications)", "DEXA scan for body composition (altered lean mass-to-fat ratio)", "Scoliosis screening with spine X-ray"],
