      correct: 1,
      rationale: "Cardiac muscle combines features of both skeletal (striated sarcomere pattern for powerful contraction) and smooth (involuntary, autorhythmic) muscle. Intercalated discs contain gap junctions that allow electrical signals to pass between cells, enabling the heart to contract as a coordinated unit."
